  "analysis": "The tail of the image file might reveal the ending colors. Let's see the last 10 lines of the file to understand the gradient direction. Also, we can use Python to sample a few rows across the image to see if it's a smooth gradient. This will help us design a simple algorithm.",
  "plan": "1. Use tail to get last 10 lines of image.ppm.\n2. Write a Python script to read the image and compute the average color for the first, middle, and last rows. We'll also compute the average color for the first, middle, and last columns to see if there's a vertical/horizontal gradient.\n3. Based on the pattern, decide on an algorithm (linear interpolation between two colors).\n4. Write a C program that generates the same gradient.\n5. Compile and test.\n\nLet's start with tail.",
