  "analysis": "This is a ray-traced scene with: (1) A blue sky background gradient, (2) A sphere in the center that's visible from around rows 810-1200 with a dark red color (51,10,10), and (3) A checkerboard ground plane with colors 67 and 152 (grayscale). The checkerboard squares appear to be 200px wide. I need to understand the exact geometry and rendering algorithm. Let me sample more precisely around the sphere boundary and the checkerboard pattern.",
  "plan": "1. Find exact sphere boundaries by scanning rows 810-900 at various x positions.\n2. Sample checkerboard pattern more densely to determine square size.\n3. Understand the sky gradient formula.\n4. Look at the 'orig' file to see if it's the original program.\n5. Then design the ray tracing algorithm.",
